		<td bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_08.gif"><font class="bfont"><font class="h1font"> sitting at the kid&#39;s table: Livonia, MI<br></font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Overall Rating:</b> </font><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><font size='1'>(5.00)</font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Author:</b> <A HREF='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=14074'>Chris "Mental Warg" Tubman</A></font><font class="afont"> <a href='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=14074&sub=1'> (Subscribe to this member)</a><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Date Submitted:</b> August 6, 2003</font><p align='justify'><blockquote><font class="bfont"> Hello All,<br />
<br />
Well after GENCON I was fairly determined to write a TR from the next local I attended assuming I would win it or at least go 3-1.  Well, I didn&#39;t do either and I wasn&#39;t going to write one but inspired by the Carny&#39;s TR I think I&#39;ll write a brief one anyway.  <br />
<br />
So it&#39;s Friday and I&#39;m at work and trying to decide what to do with my weekend it hasn&#39;t even been a week since GENCON and I&#39;m literally fiending to play cards.  Our scene here in Lansing is not really a scene at all and the tournaments that do get scheduled lately pull in a whopping 8-10 people, if were lucky.  PSQ&#39;s and the like are always good, but the locals... Not so good.  So since this last winter I had been making the occasional pilgrimage to Livonia, where there are two to three tournaments a week.  It takes about an hour.  Not too bad, but mildly annoying.  Anyway, I leave work at 5 and decide on my 30 minute drive home to tune up the deck I&#39;ve been playing and head to Livonia.  I was ambivalent as none of the Lansing boys I called could make the journey.  Guess I&#39;ll tough it out alone.<br />
<br />
Livonia has some pretty good players.... Craig Berry, Paul Mazur, Dan Clark... and they get the occasional visit from Casey Galvan (the newly crowned Game of Thrones World Champion from GENCON).  Anyway, the competition is usually pretty good, the best in Michigan anyway.  I owe a lot of my increasing LOTR skills to the Livonia crew as my rating has climbed over 100 points since I started making the trip over there in like December.<br />
<br />
Anyway, I arrive and Craig who normally directs the tournys is not there.  So Dan is filling in.  Also conspicuously absent are Paul and Casey.  Someone says Casey will show up later, which he does and apparently Paul is on vacation.  Anyway, so we have 9 players including the TD, Dan.  So with Dan as the only really good player I&#39;m feeling pretty good about the tourny.  <br />
<br />
The deck I&#39;m running is unfortunately the same pile I ran at Gen Con minus a couple of cards a side.  I think it&#39;s pretty solid, but I lost a few games to bad draws, on account of the clog factor against Dauntless which I played against A LOT.  So I trim it to a slim 30/30 build, without really sacrificing much.  Here&#39;s the decklist.<br />
<br />
Start:<br />
Frodo, RA<br />
ATAR<br />
Merry, FTS<br />
Boromir, SOD<br />
Smeagol, Slinker<br />
<br />
Ranger&#39;s Sword, Dam+1<br />
Blade of Gondor, Dam+1<br />
Frying Pan<br />
Escape<br />
Bill<br />
ATalent4NBSeen<br />
Mithril Coat<br />
Athelas x 2<br />
Sting, BH x 2<br />
Frodo&#39;s Cloak x 2<br />
Brace of Coney&#39;s x 3<br />
The Shire Countryside x 4<br />
Aragorn, WF x 3<br />
Aragorn&#39;s Bow x 2<br />
These are my people <br />
Follow Smeagol<br />
30<br />
<br />
SHADOW:<br />
Advance Uruk Patrol x 4<br />
Uruk Fighter x 3<br />
Lurtz x 2<br />
Uruk Captain x 2<br />
Uruk Assault Band x 2<br />
Uruk Vanguard x 1<br />
Uruk plains runner x 2<br />
Broad Bladed Sword x 4<br />
Uruk Spear x 3<br />
Ferocity x 3<br />
Tower of Orthanc x 2<br />
Saruman&#39;s Power x 1<br />
Saruman, SOTE x 1<br />
30<br />
<br />
Site Path<br />
The Riddermark<br />
Uruk Camp (BattleGround)<br />
Barrows of Edoras (cycle and set-up)<br />
White Rocks (BattleGround)<br />
Deep of the Helm (BG)<br />
Great Hall (BG)<br />
Hornburg Causeway (BG)<br />
Valley of Saruman (no TreeBeard/Dreary thanks)<br />
Orthanc Balcony(BG/pull Saruman)<br />
<br />
Anyway, the fellowship plays a lot like Dauntless Wingfoot, when you&#39;re up against Nazgul and Uruks, having a moderate choke, but Smeagol acts as your early stealths and midgame you can use boromir/ merry to beat Nazguls with Gorn and move again, healing all the exertions with the braces/ countrysides or the cloak/ countrysides... All the healing makes this deck stronger against uruk archery and other wounding strats like Sauron.  These are my people, you have to hold until all your countrysides are out and your looking to make that final double for the win.  If you get it early stuff it with the barrows, chances are you&#39;ll deck yourself around 7 anyway.  The shadow is designed mostly to stop your opponent and has answers for Wingfoot/ archery decks (Broad bladed sword), Rohan (uruk spear), and even Ents (large fierce dam+1 uruks with Captains for recursion).  Anyway, its follow smeagol that really keeps the shadow strong, when you pass them and they continue to play on your battlegrounds.  Anyway, enough strat babble, on to the games.<br />
<br />
I have to warn you all the details are not that clear, I didn&#39;t take notes and it&#39;s been five days.  I apologize in advance.<br />
<br />
ROUND 1  Me (1811) vs. Matt King (1693)<br />
<br />
I think I&#39;ve played Matt once or twice before and I don&#39;t remember him beating me before, but I could be wrong.  Anyway, we start the game and he bids 4 to my 0.  He starts the Westfold with the Exiled King.  Next thing I know he has I think 7 companions including (Boromir LOG, Legolas DH, Gimli LB, Sam SOH, Gandalf Mithrandir, Gorn, and Frodo).  So at this point I&#39;m a little impressed, but I do have an Uruk Vanguard in my hand and he&#39;s moving into my site 2 battleground.  So I drop I think Lurtz and the Vanguard, the pool was ridiculous.  He loses a couple of guys (Sam and Legolas), takes two on gandalf and stops.  I drop Wingfoot, follow smeagol, and some other junk. and move to 2, he plays Orc Bowmen... Now I&#39;ve played Sauron with this deck before and not had any trouble, but I feel I need to move before he gets all of his conditions rolling... also taking the lead early takes pressure off of my fellowship for the late game.  So I follow smeagol my 3, and move, he drops another Orc Bowmen and an orc, I take a couple of wounds and stop.  He moves into three after healing Mithrandir (KIE and Hard Choice) and I don&#39;t play too much a uruk fighter with a spear or a sword or something and I blow a pump to cycle.  He stops.  So I drop gorns bow and a brace, frying pan and bill, I think I played Mithril Coat at this site, but then proceeded to forget the archery -1 gametext for the next three to four sites... doh! Anyway, I think I dropped my second countryside and a cloak, Baggins Heirloom, I&#39;m not really sure, but I was relatively set- up using the Barrows to net a few more cards. So I move into 4, and here&#39;s the first big mistake... He drops Grishnak and some other chode and uses Grish&#39;s text, I thinking I have a ton of burden removal and don&#39;t want him drawing into Hates, and Bowmen, etc. elect to add the two burdens. I then off Grishnak with Merry&#39;s pan after the other one dies to archery, I think he exerted him for UTWE.  So I elect to move again and get the jump, exerting Smeagol for follow smeagol playing the Deep of the Helm and exerting frodo for UTWE.  He plays a lonely Morgul Hunter.  I think, no problem... he takes an archery, and I assign to Gorn.  Now here&#39;s where the Grishnak Burdens owned me.  He plays Enduring Evil... So 14 on 5 and me being the Jackass that I am exert Merry twice to make Gorn 8 again... Of course he plays a second one and Gorn bites it.  Now if I was intelligent and actually concerned with the possibility of a fellowship loss I would have been extra cautious and exerted Boromir to make Merry a 7 first and then No Problem, but I&#39;m dumb.  Losing a companion in this deck is kind of big, especially that particualr companion since I need to use These are my People in this match for that extra late game healing.  Oh well, I could go on to tell you how my uruks pounded on him site after site. How I singled the rest of the way, or how he had Gandalf (with 3 wounds who would take a fourth) and frodo at site 7 with 7 dead companions, and how I would most likely have killed him at 8, but I doubled twice early and anything my shadow did is moot.  Anyway, the highlight for me after losing Gorn was using his Desperate Defense of the Ring to cycle my useless Gorn cards.  So I lose at nine with two cheesy orcs on Frodo, the Enduring Evil in Matt&#39;s hand was not needed. This after having some Sauron orc I&#39;ve never seen before exert my Merry in the Manuver by removing 3.  This happened at site 7 and at site 9 for the extra wound for the win... Oh and I should mention it was up to four UTWE and 3 Bowmen when I left site 7.  I think I managed my wounds and healing really well at the end, finally remembering Mithril coat at site 8 I think, but forgetting the Coat from site 4 to 7, probably cost me the game... well that and the loss of Aragorn.  <br />
<br />
FL (+1/+1)<br />
<br />
props: Vanguard at site 2... something you don&#39;t see everyday<br />
<br />
slops: Double Enduring Evil= UGLY!  Me for not expecting Enduring Evil in a Sauron wounding deck.<br />
<br />
Round 2 Me (1811) vs. Dan Clark (2075)  Now I don&#39;t know how this pairing happened.  I thought maybe Dan lost, but no he informed me that he was just &quot;paired down&quot;.  Anyway, some history between Dan and I before I get into the game.  I think Dan beat me the first time I played him... Since then I am on a like 6-0 streak against Dan, especially in big events.  I beat him in an Ohio territorial game, in a PSQ, and even Day 2 worlds... though, he did give me a takeback on the site 6 sanctuary heal, but he showed up 5 minutes late for our game so technically I could have taken a FW by default.  Anyway, I knew sooner or later Dan has to beat me!  I mean he took 2nd in the Continentals, he&#39;s rated 2075... How does he not beat me.... Well my suspicions were right.  The worst thing about this game was that I felt I was in control the entire time and then this illusion was conveniently swept away.<br />
<br />
On to the game.... I could give a lot of details, but I&#39;ll try to keep it brief and to the point.  It started out great with Dan starting four Hobbits bidding high pulling Gorn, KIE, etc.etc.  Dan had three promises out by site 4... That&#39;s when I played Saruman&#39;s power...soooo good!  Anyway, Dan was playing moria swarms with Cave Troll and Gollum, the new one... He also had two copies of They stole it and two They are Comings so he had no problems cycling his 90 card deck... Now I moved slowly one site at a time... I do alright against Moria decks as long as I single until I get certain things set up, once I get Gorn&#39;s bow the Frying Pan, and Blade of Gondor, nothing is stacking anywhere... The Troll goes conveniently on Smeagol... and Follow Smeagol lets me avoid the Cavern Entrance.  Anyway, Dark Places, Snows, and the site 9 sneak bomb can all be problematic... But so far Dan&#39;s Deck had not displayed the capability of posing those threats.  So skip to the important stuff.  I finally get follow smeagol at site 5 and after giving him a pretty severe beating at Helms Deep decide its time to start moving, I double into six without much of a problem, playing my battleground site 6 and playing my site 7 in regroup.  He move into six takes a bit more and has to stop to heal.  I move into 7 still no Dark Places, but the Cave Troll convinces me to stop and shoot for the Double into nine.  So Dan doubles into 8 after my shadow comes up a little short.  So I reconcile and deck myself... I don&#39;t bother with these are my people as I have a cloak and after discarding a brace have no wounds... So I play everything out and have one card left in my hand, the second Frodo&#39;s cloak.  I figure this will be a cake walk as he isn&#39;t close enough to deck himself and pull out the sneak bomb.  Anyway, at site 8 things go horribly awry... He plays like Gollum and two or three orcs... I wipe out the orcs no problem, and put Gollum on Smeagol, as I had all game to avoid the wounds from They Stole it.  As smart as that is here&#39;s the dumb part.  He discards a card to make Gollum plus 2, I exert Frodo to make Gollum -2, card, exert, card, exert... It gets really dumb!  So dan&#39;s down to one card and makes some relaxed comment about, &quot; Your not taking wounds anyway...&quot; and I&#39;m like yeah I guess this is pointless... So I quit exerting and he passes... He then says Regroups.... And I&#39;m thinking I saw him discard the Black Traitor earlier and if I map my site 9 he can play hime with staff from the discard... I have no burdens so lets take a chance and see if he&#39;s playing the Palantir Chamber.... so I pass... In Retrospect the intelligent thing to have done is exert his Gollum thrice to play my next site with follow smeagol and then kill him with Wingfoot for one less minion at nine... But I&#39;m as I said before a Jackass... So after I pass Dan gets this huge Feces eating grin on his face and removes five pool and slaps Master Broke His Promise on the table... And I&#39;m glad I couldn&#39;t see the look on my face, as it probably was a look of utter disbelief, like seeing a midget take on five dudes in a porno. Anyway, incase your infamiliar with the card it says, &quot;regroup: exert Gollum three times to wound every companion and make the move limit -1.&quot;  The wounding wasn&#39;t a thing, but with one card in hand I kinda needed to move into site 9 for the win.... I really couldn&#39;t believe what had happened... Oh well, Dan roll&#39;s into site 9 and I throw my cloak down removing 2 pool just for laughs.  I asked Dan after the game if he had been holding it all game, and he laughs and says no I just drew it.<br />
<br />
FL (+1/+2)<br />
<br />
Props:  Dan for finally breaking his streak against me.... Dan for not blowing snot on himself during the game.  Master Broke his Promise for not only working, but actually winning a game.<br />
<br />
Slops: Me for having tunnel vision, and thinking nothing could stop me from winning on the double to nine.  Not remembering that follow smeagol can also exert Gollum.... Doh!<br />
<br />
So at this point I think I&#39;m tied for last with some 10 year old or something, but Dan realizing I drove an hour, gives him the bye instead of me, thanks.<br />
<br />
Round 3 Me (1811) vs. I think his name was William... I don&#39;t know he was probably 10 - 12 years old.<br />
<br />
So this game was kind of uneventful... He played Ents and a lot of them and my shadow just kind of owned him all game long.  His trackers weren&#39;t doing too much to me.  And despite having like 8 cards on Frodo he never saw a skirmish, much less had a Vengeance played on him.  In the end he tried to double into nine for the win... But was down to three Ents, two of them exhausted, and Frodo... I had a Patrol on the table and dropped a captain, Uruk plains runner w spear, Captained a Vanguard and grabbed Saruman, SoTE... and still had pool... Both Towers kicked in plus I had saved some at 8... ANyway, death ensued as Frodo got eaten by four uruks in the fierce...<br />
<br />
FW (+3/+5)<br />
<br />
props:  William played really well for his age.<br />
<br />
slops: none really....<br />
<br />
Round 4 Me (1811) vs. some other kid probably like 14 or 15.. I can&#39;t remember his name Eddie maybe?<br />
<br />
Anyway.... I don&#39;t want to bore you with the details of this game.  He was playing Ring Bound Rangers and Easterlings... He choked me pretty good early and anything I could play was eaten by Faramir...Meanwhile, he was adding quite a few burdens... via Gathering to the Summons... and a New Fear... I hadn&#39;t seen that one played before... But he was getting frustrated I think as I removed his burdens almost as quickly as he added them... and his minions were not really a problem... anyway when he moved into site 5 he took quite a beating from large fierce uruks... I think he played a companion at four so the pool was supple. I couldn&#39;t quite kill him at six and then again at seven... I moved into nine after using these are my people at seven and healing everyone and more importantly going down to zero burdens... <br />
<br />
FW (+3/+8)<br />
<br />
props: His deck had potential... I found out he doesn&#39;t have a lot of great cards... So it was a good build for what he had.  My deck having the versatility to handle a burden deck without any worries.<br />
<br />
slops: not being able to finish off his crippled fellowship at 6 or 7.<br />
<br />
<br />
So that was the tourny... I didn&#39;t check to see where I placed, but Dan didn&#39;t win it either, he took 2nd or 3rd (two 3-1&#39;s) and Tony took first.  I think its the first time Tony&#39;s taken a tourny for a while and he was pretty charged up about his deck.  Afterwords Tony comes up to me and says hey you want to play... (note: this is basically the same deck he played last time I went to Livonia, but &quot;tuned up&quot;)  It&#39;s rangers with direct damage and Nazgul&#39;s, and last time I owned him.<br />
<br />
I won&#39;t go in to details but in summary... I owned a witchking with Pale blade and moved again at one point... Everytime I dropped a large Uruk with a Broad Bladed sword someone died, usually two companions.  I had him down to just aragorn and Frodo, then just Frodo... Then I decided to double for the win just to show him how much I disrespect Nazgul.... It&#39;s a good thing I did cause he had two or three companions in his hand he was going to drop with Frodo and again I had pretty much decked myself....<br />
<br />
So of course now my deck runs like a well oiled machine and I own the guy who won the tournament.. after getting smoked twice and then playing with the children.  Oh well... It beats sitting at home on a Friday night anyway.<br />
<br />
Until next time peace.... and don&#39;t make promises to little twisted obsessive hobbit-like creatures and then go breaking them!<br />
